Good laws should execute Good laws in a well-regulated state; at least, if the same legislature which provides the laws doth not provide for the execution of Good laws, Good laws act as Graham would do, if Graham should form all the parts of a clock in the most exquisite manner, yet put Good laws so together that a clock could not go.
